      • insertFeature

        long insertFeature​(long fsid,
                   long fid,
                   FeatureDefinition2 def,
                   long version)
            throws DataStoreException
        Inserts the specified feature into the data store.
        Parameters:
        fsid - The feature set ID that the feature will belong to.
        fid - The desired feature ID. If FEATURE_ID_NONE is specified, the data store will assign a unique ID.
        def - The feature definition
        version - The desired feature version. If FEATURE_VERSION_NONE is specified, the data store will assign a version of 1L.
        Returns:
        The ID of the feature inserted
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If fsid is not an ID for a feature set that belongs to the data store

      • insertFeature

        long insertFeature​(Feature feature)
            throws DataStoreException
        Inserts the specified feature into the data store.
        Parameters:
        feature - The feature to be inserted. The feature must have its feature set ID set to a valid value. If the feature ID is FEATURE_ID_NONE, the data store will assign a unique ID; if the feature version is FEATURE_VERSION_NONE, a version of 1L will be assigned.
        Returns:
        The ID of the feature inserted
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If feature set ID of the feature is not an ID for a feature set that belongs to the data store

      • insertFeatures

        void insertFeatures​(FeatureCursor features)
             throws DataStoreException
        Performs bulk insertion of the specified features.
        Parameters:
        features - The features to be inserted. Each feature must have its feature set ID set to a valid value. If the feature ID is FEATURE_ID_NONE, the data store will assign a unique ID; if the feature version is FEATURE_VERSION_NONE, a version of 1L will be assigned.
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If feature set ID of a feature is not an ID for a feature set that belongs to the data store
